Hello Parent_B—thank you for reaching out and for your thoughtful questions.

In the classroom, we’re primarily play-based with gentle structure: we use predictable routines (arrival, circle time, small-group activities, lunch/rest) while learning goals are embedded through guided play, language-rich interactions, and hands-on exploration.

Outdoor time is a daily priority whenever weather allows. We balance free play (gross motor, risk-aware climbing/running) with occasional teacher-led activities (nature walks, simple games), and we emphasize safe boundaries and cooperative play.

For social-emotional development, we focus on naming feelings, modeling calm conflict resolution, and coaching children through turn-taking and repair (“what can we do to make it better?”). We also partner closely with families so strategies are consistent between home and school.

When considering families for placement, we value: (1) strong home–school communication, (2) reliability/consistency with attendance and routines, and (3) openness to collaborating on a child’s individual needs.

For steps/deadlines: families should be ready to submit an application as soon as they feel we’re a fit, since interest can move quickly. If you’re comfortable sharing, it would help to know your child’s age and intended start date, any schedule constraints, and where Nursery_C currently sits in your preference order.
